The paper proposes a method for real-time 3D reconstruction and localization for actively controlled endoscopic capsule robots. This involves combining magnetic and vision-based localization, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The method also involves non-rigid deformations based frame-to-model map fusion, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method using different trajectories and endoscopic cameras, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) for optimization and generalization purposes.
